# What Changed in Databricks?

The old Community Edition had:

```text
Clusters
```

The new Free Edition provides:

```text
Serverless Compute
```

behind the scenes.

So you won't create clusters manually.

Databricks manages compute for you.

---

# Interview Insight

This is actually useful to know.

### Traditional Databricks

```text
User creates cluster
      ↓
Notebook runs on cluster
```

### Serverless Databricks

```text
Notebook
      ↓
Databricks provisions compute automatically
```

Less infrastructure management.

